tourBios.exmtStatus: Finished T123 at Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament
tourBios.curYearHigh: Was a non-member of the Web.com Tour to start 2015 yet wound up playing in nine events, making six cuts. Finished 85th on the Regular Season money list...Got into his first event in early June when he successfully Monday-qualified for the Greater Dallas Open with a 65 at the GC of Dallas. Opened with 65-69 and stood T15 after 36 holes. A bogey-free 67 propelled him to T5 with one round to play. Added a 66 on Sunday, coming up two shots shy of champion Tyler Aldridge, but collected a check for $44,000 to debut at No. 59 on the money list. The T2 finish was the best performance by a Monday qualifier on Tour since Sebastian Cappelen's win at the 2014 Air Capital Classic...Added one more top 25 at the Stonebrae Classic in July...Was tied for No. 1 at the end of the Regular Season with Trey Mullinax in the Par-5 Scoring Average stat (4.48).
